  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">First People&apos;s Justice - Indigenous Justice Reform</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Oxfam Australia&#x2019;s Indigenous Justice Reform program works with Indigenous coalitions that operate at a state and federal level to lobby for law reform to reduce Australia&#x2019;s very high rates of Indigenous incarceration, which are among the highest rates in the world. These coalitions have are also calling for, and in some cases initiating, &#x201C;justice reinvestment&#x201D; programs which emphasise preventative support in communities.&#xA0; The program also supports Indigenous-led groups that are advocating for a smarter approach to justice for Indigenous Australians.</narrative>
  </description>
